<p>jobs of the day takes place namely the issue of rum.<br/>Sometimes after this we turn in for an hour or so, but generally work starts immediately, one of the first duties is tidying &amp; cleaning up the trench, empty bully tins, biscuits paper &amp; etc form the greater part of the rubbish, then set to &amp; clean our rifles, after this breakfast.<br/>As a rule each man cooks his own, though in some of the quieter places the cooks do the work.<br/>After breakfast comes the pick &amp; shovel work for no trench no matter how good it might be is never finished, there is always the parapet to be strengthened or new communication trenches to be dug or other damage to be repaired<br/>Sometimes you can hear old</p>
